      "content": "That feeling is totally normal, and it's actually a great sign that you're thinking about the long term. A common rule of thumb is to keep about 3–6 months of your *living* expenses in a high-yield savings account, but you can go higher if you have a longer horizon or a larger emergency need. Since you have $15,000, you might consider keeping it there until you hit a milestone like $25,000 or 6 months of your total expenses, depending on your personal budget. If you keep it for a few years, you'll be earning compound interest, which means the interest you earn each year will also start earning interest in the next year. It's a bit of a \"wait-and-see\" strategy, but it's a solid way to let your money work for you while you focus on other financial goals.",
